ce, and studying how narratives make sense of experience.Investigating production processes in the cultural industries, and the consumption and assimilation of cultural products by audiences and fans.Taking both quantitative and qualitative approaches to the study of cultural life.Analysing visual images and both spoken and written forms of discourse.Exploring cultural memory and historical representation.Key FeaturesA unique guide to research methods in Cultural StudiesExplores key methods of research, with examples of how to pursue (or not to pursue) a particular method.Expert contributors include Martin Barker, Aeron Davis, David Deacon, Emily Keightley, Steph Lawler, Anneke Meyer, Virginia Nightingale and Sarah Pink.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 0aCulturexMethodology. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aREFERENCE / Research.2bisacsh1 aBarker, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Aeron, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeacon, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeightley, Emily, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLawler, Steph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, Anneke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNightingale, Virginia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPickering, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPink, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078046840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978074863119340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748631193423Coveruhttps://